# Git Workflow

> L2 instruction module — loaded when working on branches, commits, or PRs.

## Creating Branches

```bash
git checkout {{conventions.default_branch}}
git pull origin {{conventions.default_branch}}
git checkout -b {{conventions.branch_pattern}}
```

## Commit Message Format

Format: **{{conventions.commit_format}}**

```
<type>(<scope>): <subject>

<body>

Closes {{conventions.branch_pattern}}
```

**Types**: `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `style`, `refactor`, `test`, `chore`

## Pull Request Guidelines

- Reference the ticket/issue in the PR title
- Include a summary of changes
- Add screenshots for UI changes
- Ensure CI passes before requesting review
- Squash commits on merge

